The paper deals with image fusion, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method uses a deep decomposition approach, which is a popular technique in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves matrix factorization and optimization, which are common topics in machine learning and optimization, respectively. Hence, cs.MM (Mathematical Methods in Computer Science) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an adaptive fusion strategy, which involves decision-making and reasoning, indicating that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves signal processing and information theory, which are common topics in cs.IT (Information Theory).
